<p>So I was debugging a program that was showing a Segfault. I ran gdb and from the backtrace I see that the value of (this) changes on calling.</p>  <p>The calling function is of the type</p>  <pre><code>Foo::funcName1() const {     return Bar::funcName2()-&gt;calledFunc(); }   </code></pre>  <p>The called function is of the form</p>  <pre><code>Foo2::calledFunc() const {     /*      Some stuff     */ } </code></pre>  <p>According to the backtrace I have</p>  <pre><code>0x00007ff456a9ec9f in Blah::Meh::funcName1() const (this=0x1f59b40) 0x00007ff44fee181c in Foo2::calledFunc() const (this=0x0) </code></pre>  <p>How can this be happening ?</p>